				[===   MooLibrary   ===]

What is it?
-----------

The MooLibrary is my personal class library that I have built for Zend Framework.


Library Components:
-------------------

  - Flash Messenger
    + Link: http://jamandcheese-on-phptoast.com/2009/11/03/custom-flash-messenger-for-zend-framework/
    + Files: Controller/Action/Helper/Messenger.php
             View/Helper/Messenger.php

  - Image View Helper
    + Link: http://jamandcheese-on-phptoast.com/2009/10/15/image-view-helper-for-zend-framework/
    + Files: View/Helper/Html/Image.php
             View/Helper/Html/Image/ActionInterface.php

  - Date View Helper
    + Files: View/Helper/Date.php

  - Text View Helper
    + Files: View/Helper/Text/CropSentence.php

  - Table View Helper
    + Files: View/Helper/Html/Table.php
             View/Helper/Html/Table/RowInterface.php

  - Alternate Row Class View Helper
    + Files: View/Helper/Html/RowClass.php

  - Page Tile Action Helper
    + Files: Controller/Action/Helper/PageTitle.php

  - AjaxAction Action Helper
    + Files: Controller/Action/Helper/AjaxAction.php

  - Mail
    + Files: Mail.php
             Mail/Resource.php
             Mail/Resource/Default.php

  - Utility
    + Files: Utility.php

System Requirements:
--------------------

Zend Framework 1.10 or later
PHP5 or later

Installation:
-------------
1. Place the files in a directory library/Moo/
2. Add library/ directory to your include paths
3. Register the namespace Moo with Zend_Loader_Autoloader

